1. Create Prj
2. VCS -> Enable Version Control Integration
    2.1 Select Git

3. Create Python file, add code
4. RMB -> Git -> +Add (Ctrl+Alt+A)
    or Add to .gitignore

Green - added
Blue - edited

5. VSC -> Commit (Ctrl+K)
    5.1 Commit msg


Prev code view:
Alt+9 -> Log -> RMB -> Checkout Revision

Ctrl+Tab - tabs list

Undo changes:
VCS -> Git -> RollBack (Ctrl+ALT+Z)


Push to Git:
1. Create New repository
2. Copy URL
3. VCS -> Git -> Remotes (name: origin, URL: paste)
4. VCS -> Git -> Push (Ctrl+Shift+K)

Add branch:
1. LMB master (right bottom)
2. New Branch -> name

Merge:
1. LMB master (right bottom) -> master -> Checkout
2. LMB master (right bottom) -> branch-1 name -> Merge into Current
3. LMB master (right bottom) -> branch-2 name -> Merge into Current
4. Conflicts -> Merge...
5. Push

Update from Git:
1. VCS -> Update Project (Ctrl+T)
2. Rebase
3. Ok


